Thread a bead onto the outer left strand. Thread the bead and push against the base of the braid. Then cross the left strand over the middle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/de/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-7.jpg/v4-460px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-7.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/de/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-7.jpg/v4-760px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-7.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":505.27472527472526,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Do the same but with the right strand this time. Thread the bead onto the outer right strand, push against the base of the braid, and cross over the middle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ce/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-8.jpg/v4-460px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-8.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ce/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-8.jpg/v4-760px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-8.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":505.27472527472526,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Rotate between the outer right and outer left strands. Thread the beads before crossing the strands over the middle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/17/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-9.jpg/v4-460px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-9.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/17/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-9.jpg/v4-760px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-9.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":505.27472527472526,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Complete braiding the beads in. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f0/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-10.jpg/v4-460px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-10.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f0/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-10.jpg/v4-760px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-10.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":505.27472527472526,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Leave a tail of about another inch (2.5cm) or so of braided cord. Measure against the wrist to ensure the bracelet isn’t too small or too big, then secure with an overhand knot. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f7/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-12.jpg/v4-460px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-12.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f7/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-12.jpg/v4-760px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-12.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":505.27472527472526,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Trim the two shortest strands completely off. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c2/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-13.jpg/v4-460px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-13.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c2/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-13.jpg/v4-760px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-13.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":505.27472527472526,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Butt it up against the braided section, then secure with another overhand knot. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/31/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-15.jpg/v4-460px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-15.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/31/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-15.jpg/v4-760px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-15.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":505.27472527472526,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Trim any excess cording. Be careful not to cut the knot. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/23/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-16.jpg/v4-460px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-16.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/23/Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-16.jpg/v4-760px-Make-DIY-Wrist-Candy-Step-16.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":505.27472527472526,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
